    Worker

    class MainWorker
extends java.lang.Object
implements Worker
    Main worker class of the application - comprises doWork(), the business logic method, as well as the primary utility methods.

    References & libraries:
    Apache Maven Invoker. [Online]. Available: https://maven.apache.org/shared/maven-invoker/

    • Constructor Detail

      • MainWorker

        MainWorker(java.lang.String projectPath,
           java.lang.String pitStatReportsPath,
           boolean pitStatReportsPathRelative,
           boolean createTimestampDirectory,
           boolean noHuman,
           boolean zipOutput,
           boolean noMachine,
           java.lang.String startCommit,
           java.lang.String endCommit,
           int maxRollbacks,
           int threadsNo)
    throws java.lang.Exception
        Parameters:
        projectPath - String, holds the path of the target project
        pitStatReportsPath - String, holds the paths where the PitStat reports will be saved
        pitStatReportsPathRelative - boolean, records whether the path for the PitStat reports is absolute or relative to the project path (true if path is relative)
        createTimestampDirectory - boolean, records whether the PitStat reports are to be placed into a timestamped subdirectory (true is timestamp directory is to be created)
        noHuman - boolean, records whether human readable output should be created (false if human readable output is to be created)
        zipOutput - boolean, records whether machine readable output is to be saver as zip compressed archive
        noMachine - boolean, records whether machine readable output is to be created; only relevant where both human and machine readable output is available (false if machine readable output is to be created)
        startCommit - String, holds the hash string of the start commit (most recent)
        endCommit - String, holds the hash string of the end commit (oldest)
        maxRollbacks - int, holds the number of rollback to be performed
        threadsNo - int, holds the number of threads that will be passed to PIT
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
